WHAT IS IT?
-----------

  'Arrowz' is a game where your goal is to rotate arrows between
a 'pressed down' space and a coloured tile like the one shown on
the uppermost position in the column located at the right of the
game board. When the arrows form a way to the required tile, a
'path' is then formed (all the arrows used to make that path are
pressed down) to that tile. That tile then becomes the next
starting tile.

  The more arrows that are used to make a path between the two
tiles, the more points you will get, but beware! There are holes
that must be avoided, and if arrows are positioned in such a way
that they lead to a hole, the game is over.

  Continue to get to the other coloured tiles until you finish
each game board.

  Have fun!

